   <!--
      I've written the possessive of Цѣсарь as Цѣсарѥвъ, with jotated ѥ, because
      1) it's etymologically correct, 2) it's in Cejtlin, and 3) it's consistent with our
      writing forms like глаголѥши. But if we do that, should we also write inflected
      forms with ѥ, e.g., Isg Цѣсарѥмь? Historically it's a palatal /r/ < /rj/, and not
      just a soft /r/. On the other hand, it's sort a superfluous distinction to make in
      EESl, where palatal and palatalized merged with the jer shift. On a third hand, 
      we're reconstucting etymological jers, that is, a state of the language before the
      completion of the jer shift. On a fourth hand, if we write глаголѥши, we should
      also be writing землѥю, полѥмь, конѥмь.
   -->
